events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Donte DiVincenzo scored 31 points, Miles McBride had 26 and the New York Knicks beat the Brooklyn Nets 105-93 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: DiVincenzo scores 31 points as New York Knicks beat Brooklyn Nets 105-93

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox hit tying and go-ahead free throws with 21.2 seconds left and finished with 31 points, and Keon Ellis added another free throw in the final seconds as the Sacramento Kings beat the Orlando Magic 109-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De’Aaron Fox and Keon Ellis hit key free throws to help the Kings beat the Magic 109-107

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray made a season-high seven 3-pointers while scoring 28 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Charlotte Hornets 132-91 on Saturday night to strengthen their hold on the final spot in the Eastern Conference play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hot-shooting Murray's 28 points power Hawks past Bridges, Hornets 132-91

headlines.description: — Deni Avdija scored 22 points and grabbed 13 rebounds, Kyle Kuzma made some big baskets down the stretch to compensate for a rough shooting performance and the Washington Wizards handed the Toronto Raptors their 10th consecutive loss, 112-109 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards win their 2nd in a row and hand Raptors their 10th consecutive loss

headlines.description: — Whether Jayson Tatum is missing a game or Jaylen Brown is sitting out the next night, the Boston Celtics just keep rolling along. Make it nine straight wins now for the team with the NBA's best record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Hauser, Horford lead way as NBA-leading Celtics beat Bulls 124-113 for 9th straight win

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 41 points, Fred VanVleet added 10 3-pointers and a season-high 34 and the Houston Rockets made a season-best 27 3-pointers to beat the Utah Jazz 147-119 on Saturday night for their eighth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 41, Rockets beat Jazz 147-119 for eighth straight victory

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 32 points before sitting out the fourth quarter and the Phoenix Suns never trailed in steamrolling the San Antonio Spurs 131-106 on Saturday night to help their playoff positioning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 32 points and Suns never trail in steamrolling Spurs 131-106

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson scored 23 points, Aaron Gordon had 22 points and 12 rebounds and the Denver Nuggets defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 114-111 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets edge youthful Trail Blazers 114-111 after Portland starts 5 rookies
